 United States President Donald Trump said on Monday that it looked like Iran was responsible for attacks over the weekend on Saudi Arabian oil plants, but he wants to avoid war. “It is certainly looking that way at this moment,” Trump told reporters when asked if he believes Iran carried out the attack. “With all that being said, we’d certainly [will] like to avoid war”, he said. “I don’t want war with anybody but we’re prepared more than anybody.” Aljazeera reported that Washington has blamed Tehran for the attacks, which cut five per cent of world crude oil production. Continue reading US certainly will like to avoid war with Iran ―Trump at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard